  <name>ZorinShot</name>
  <summary>Wayland-compatible screenshot tool with autosave and annotation</summary>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      ZorinShot is a modern, Wayland-compatible screenshot tool designed specifically for 
      Linux desktop environments. It provides an intuitive interface for capturing, 
      annotating, and saving screenshots with advanced autosave functionality.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Wayland-native screenshot capture with X11 fallback support</li>
      <li>Interactive region selection with visual feedback</li>
      <li>Comprehensive annotation tools (pen, arrow, rectangle, text)</li>
      <li>Autosave with customizable default locations</li>
      <li>Quick Save and Save As functionality</li>
      <li>Clipboard integration for instant sharing</li>
      <li>Persistent settings and preferences</li>
      <li>Keyboard shortcuts for efficient workflow</li>
      <li>Support for PNG and JPEG formats</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Perfect for content creators, developers, and anyone who needs to capture and 
      annotate screenshots regularly. ZorinShot eliminates the friction of traditional 
      screenshot workflows with its intelligent autosave system and streamlined interface.
    </p>
  </description>
  
